The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Air force conclave

 New Delhi, April 18: Fine-tuning a weapons acquisitions programme and chalking up joint manoeuvres with the navy and the army are at the top of the agenda for a commanders? conference of the Indian Air Force that began here today, reports our special correspondent.

 The conference is being held in the background of the US offer to sell F-16 Fighting Falcon aircraft and also the F/A 18 Hornet to India. The IAF is in the market to buy 126 multirole combat aircraft and is examining aircraft from the US, Sweden, Russia and France.

 Air force sources said the meet would also make an assessment of threat perceptions and take stock of the inventory and the maintenance of ageing aircraft. 




